1
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:40,840
Wasan.

2
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:43,100
Let's talk.

3
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,440
Didn't I tell you?

4
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:46,000
I have nothing to talk to you about.

5
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,730
I know you want a peaceful life.

6
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:50,330
But are you really at peace?

7
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:52,530
What do you mean?

8
00:00:55,360 --> 00:00:56,890
This is your father, right?

9
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:06,330
How do you have a photo of my father?

10
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:09,640
Your father was a security guard at the Dai family shipyard, right?

11
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:11,840
When the Dai family caught fire five years ago,

12
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,100
where was your father?

13
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:18,930
Why are you asking this now?

14
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:20,360
My father is dead.

15
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:21,340
Where is he?

16
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:22,320
How would I know?

17
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:23,520
My mother is dead too.

18
00:01:24,360 --> 00:01:25,960
She died in that fire.

19
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:29,240
The next day, your father was shot dead for no reason.

20
00:01:29,240 --> 00:01:30,600
The police didn't even care about it.

21
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:31,560
Do you think this is a coincidence?

22
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:33,200
What does it matter if it's a coincidence or not?

23
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:34,240
He's dead. Dead!

24
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,560
That's why we need the truth.

25
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:36,479
Are you okay?

26
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:37,680
Investigate?

27
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:39,000
Even if you find out the truth,

28
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,120
they can still cover it up

29
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:41,000
and turn black into white.

30
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,600
That's why we have to find it.

31
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:43,320
If they are evil,

32
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:44,479
we will be more evil.

33
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:45,800
If they are ruthless,

34
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,200
we will be more ruthless.

35
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:51,400
When my mother burned to death in the fire,

36
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:53,240
I could even hear her crying out.

37
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:57,520
Over the past five years,

38
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:00,200
my heart has never been at peace.

39
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,320
Ou Shaowen,

40
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,200
your pain

41
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:14,020
is just nostalgia.

42
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:17,100
My pain is that I killed her with my own hands.

43
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:20,280
Angwei,

44
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:23,820
have you ever really asked yourself,

45
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:26,560
do you truly love her,

46
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:30,420
or do you just want to keep her around to atone for your sins?

47
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:33,920
She doesn't need your protection.

48
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:35,400
What she wants now is the truth,

49
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:38,600
not to live under your so-called umbrella of protection.

50
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:41,500
Your love is completely selfish.

51
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:45,320
Your father also died a mysterious death.

52
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:46,840
Don't you want revenge?

53
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,290
I'm begging you.

54
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:58,880
Please.

55
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,520
What can I do for you?

56
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:19,380
Tell me.

57
00:03:20,360 --> 00:03:21,490
I need you to tell me,

58
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:24,340
what did your father see that day?

59
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:29,640
That night,

60
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:33,120
my father said he forgot something at the shipyard

61
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:34,780
and had to go back to get it.

62
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,079
But in the middle of the night,

63
00:03:36,079 --> 00:03:37,360
he rushed back

64
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:39,020
empty-handed, with nothing.

65
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,560
He was terrified.

66
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:42,370
He said he saw...

67
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:48,280
He saw two men in black taking gasoline into the cabin.

68
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,620
And heard them say,

69
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:51,050
Brother Lapeng said

70
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,730
it's Mrs. Ruan's order.

71
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:55,360
We must burn both of these women to death today.

72
00:03:56,079 --> 00:03:57,740
Mrs. Ruan is really ruthless.

73
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:01,120
My father thought about it all night.

74
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,980
He went to the police the next day,

75
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:04,330
and never came back.

76
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:14,320
Dailing, leave me alone. Run!

77
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:16,320
Run.

78
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:18,760
Run.

79
00:04:20,079 --> 00:04:22,079
Run, Dailing.

80
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,920
Run.

81
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:25,680
It's been five years.

82
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:27,280
Five whole years.

83
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:29,440
I've been living like a clown.

84
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:30,800
Hiding everywhere.

85
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,400
I want revenge too.

86
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,080
Before my father died.

87
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:42,159
He wrote a report letter.

88
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,320
I've been keeping it.

89
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:45,420
Wait for me.

90
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:47,380
I'll get it for you.

91
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:52,960
Wasan.

92
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,159
Wasan.

93
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:02,240
Wasan.

94
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:10,010
Are you okay?

95
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:13,940
Did you see anyone?

96
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:18,320
Young master.

97
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:20,280
I found Ruan Nila's men nearby.

98
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:24,720
Ruan Nila.

99
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,800
Contact me anytime if you need help.

100
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:44,920
Ruan Nila.

101
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:46,780
Angwei.

102
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,600
Did you kill Wa San?

103
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,400
Wa San?

104
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:52,840
Who is Wa San?

105
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,250
Don't play dumb with me.

106
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,560
Wa San had key evidence

107
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,690
of the cabin arson case from back then.

108
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:01,920
You killed him to destroy the evidence.

109
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:03,920
Is it because

110
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,640
you were the mastermind behind

111
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:07,480
that cabin arson case?

112
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:11,420
Then let me ask you.

113
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,090
What does Wa San have to do with you?

114
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:15,560
And what does the arson case from five years ago

115
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,960
have to do with you?

116
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:19,640
Why do you keep

117
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:20,760
dwelling on this?

118
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:21,320
Shut up.

119
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:24,240
Are you doing this for Feifei,

120
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,560
for the late Dailing,

121
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:27,560
to make up for your past guilt,

122
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:30,980
or because your love for the substitute reignited?

123
00:06:32,159 --> 00:06:32,720
Ang Wei.

124
00:06:33,159 --> 00:06:34,159
For this woman,

125
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:35,880
you've turned into a madman.

126
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:37,730
Are you going to use this gun

127
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:39,480
against your own family?

128
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:40,240
Ruannila,

129
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,340
is just a dog raised by our family.

130
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:45,000
Insolent!

131
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:46,200
Sir.

132
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:48,400
She killed Wasan.

133
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:50,540
Ruannila is your stepmother.

134
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,400
Disrespecting her

135
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,240
is disrespecting me.

136
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:57,840
Today you can point a gun at your stepmother.

137
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:58,760
Tomorrow,

138
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:02,640
will you fight your father?

139
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:07,040
Father.

140
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,680
Wa San is dead.

141
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,080
It's his destiny.

142
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:13,980
Once a person dies,

143
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,540
they should rest in peace.

144
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:16,440
After all,

145
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:18,800
he was one of us at Sihai Group.

146
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:21,050
Distribute the pension

147
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:23,580
and let this matter pass completely.

148
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:26,700
No one is allowed to mention it again.

149
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:27,530
Understood?

150
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:28,080
Father.

151
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,200
Master,

152
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:32,120
don't be too hard on Wei.

153
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,920
He is just a kid after all.

154
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,680
He was just bewitched by that woman.

155
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,610
Shut your mouth.

156
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,360
From today on,

157
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:44,720
you must completely cut ties with

158
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:46,400
that woman named Feifei.

159
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,600
If you can't,

160
00:07:52,159 --> 00:07:54,640
I will make her disappear forever.

161
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,040
You can't touch her.

162
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:14,050
Take him over there.

163
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,600
If a sapling grows crooked,

164
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:26,280
you must trim its branches.

165
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,040
Angwei,

166
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:48,090
do you remember?

167
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,120
When you were 3 years old,

168
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,940
you said you liked this red balloon the most.

169
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,140
I bought it for you.

170
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:57,680
You happily said, "Thank you, Dad."

171
00:08:58,400 --> 00:08:59,160
You also said

172
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:02,200
that Dad was the best person in the world,

173
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:04,720
and that you would always listen to Dad.

174
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:06,320
Back then,

175
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:07,980
how obedient you were.

176
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:10,600
You never talked back to me.

177
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:14,560
As quiet as an exquisite sculpture.

178
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:18,720
This amusement park was built for you.

179
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:20,800
Now that you've grown up,

180
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:22,880
it's also abandoned.

181
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:24,640
So what?

182
00:09:27,920 --> 00:09:29,360
But you've grown up,

183
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,460
and for the sake of a woman,

184
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:34,060
you dare to order your dad around.

185
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:41,960
You want to speak?

186
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,560
Listen more,

187
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,120
speak less.

188
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,560
Long Jiu sent me his location.

189
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:15,290
Angwei was kidnapped by Danpa.

190
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:17,610
He's locked in the old amusement park.

191
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:19,960
I owe him a favor.

192
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,320
I'll go save him.

193
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:23,380
You are not doing it to return a favor.

194
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,460
You are afraid he will die.

195
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:29,240
Besides, Danpa probably just wanted to scare him.

196
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:32,250
I'm afraid he'll die in someone else's hands.

197
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:35,880
You've never been good at lying since you were a kid.

198
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,140
After all these years,

199
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:39,520
you still haven't improved.

200
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:43,800
You don't need to take risks with me.

201
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:44,800
I'll go by myself.

202
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,860
I don't want to save him at all.

203
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:55,760
Not at all.
